title: Farrah Abraham gets more plastic surgery; 'Paranormal Activity' prank: PM Buzz
text:
Comments 
"Teen Mom" star Farrah Abraham is getting more plastic surgery , but this time she's getting her second boob job fixed. The reality TV personality (and porn star) documented her first breast augmentation on the MTV series in 2011, going from an A to a C cup, and has since gotten D-cup breasts, cheek and lip fillers, a chin implant, and rhinoplasty. Her lip implants caused her mouth to swell up, leading to an appearance on "Botched," and her third breast augmentation now aims to fix "burning and pain issues" that will be revealed on an episode of "Botched: Post Op." Hey, anything to stay in the limelight, right? » Read more at Hollywood Life . 
What happens when a real estate agent joins in on a "Paranormal Activity" prank ? Hilarity ensues. A funny video promoting the horror franchise's new film "The Ghost Dimension" shows people attending an open house in San Diego at the actual home used in the first "Paranormal Activity" movie. Ceiling lights sway, a microwave flickers, a picture frame falls and a mirror shatters, sending people screaming at they run out of the house. "Paranormal Activity: The Ghost Dimension" hits theaters Friday. 
Travis Barker says Blink-182 has recorded five new songs with Mark Hoppus and Alkaline Trio's Matt Skiba, who stepped in after a very public split with singer-guitarist Tom DeLonge. "Matt's killing it," Barker said. "He's fun to play with and write with... There's a song called 'Punk Rock Cliché' which I love the most right now. It's about friends of ours and their relationships." The drummer won't say if an album is on the way, but the band was planning on recording new music with DeLonge before. » Read more at Rolling Stone . 
And Faith No More's new music video is here after making its world premiere in Syracuse this past weekend. Syracuse University alumnus Joe Lynch ("Everly") directed the fun clip for "Sunny Side Up," and showed it first as a surprise at the Syracuse International Film Festival on Friday. Senior citizens play the metal band, which recently released its first album in 15 years after several years of reunion tours.
